Currently, when a user uploads a profile picture, we automatically downsize it to 48x48. We should save a much larger version of the user's profile picture. There should still be an upper limit, but it should be more like 500x500. There are times when we want to display a large version of the user's picture: say in the staff directory, or the user's homepage, or the User Info plugin, but we're limited to the 48x48 square version. 

We should take the upload and store the full-size version, at whatever aspect ration they upload, and also store a thumbnail version at 48x48.

We should also implement CONF-4345 along with this.

