After moving to Maven 2, I've found using "mvn idea:idea -DdownloadSources=true -DdownloadJavadocs=true" really useful, especially as it attaches the sources and Javadocs. Unfortunately this doesn't include the sources / Javadocs for Confluence.

While Javadocs could be added into the public repository, sources clearly couldn't be. I propose setting up a HTTPS repository which is authenticated using the same username and password as http://atlassian.com/my. This would mean a secured repository could be added into a developers local settings.xml.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-7644].
